				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Eysenhudt: Adaptives Kampf System" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Adaptive Combat System is a Mini Expansion for Eysenhudt to make battle more adaptive and thus more challenging. The basic thought behind the Adaptive Combat System is: the more power in arms your army &amp;ndash; the &amp;raquo;Heller Haufen&amp;laquo; &amp;ndash; is  able  to  mass,  the  more  aware  the  targets&amp;rsquo;  defenders  will  become  of your armaments. So they will most likely adapt!&amp;#10;Thus battle against the important fortified towns will become more challenging than ever (and regardless of your actual attack's potential). After you have computed your strength you determine the difficulty-level against which to compete with the help of a rotary dial and a dice roll. Each difficulty-level (the basic copper ~, the silver ~, the gold ~, the palladium ~ and the plutonium level) comes with its own set of Battle Cards and with its own die. So, in the hardest case you've to compete against a D16 with a lessened probability of rolling the lower values (but also, of course, of rolling a total failure). Thus, with increased difficulty the luck-factor (or bad-dice-roll-factor) decreases.&amp;#10;This Mini Expansion is meant to be optional and for all who want to try a new challenge when going into battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
